# Audix DSP Engine — Flagship-Level Overhaul

Full analysis and upgrade of the Audix audio processing chain, bug fixes, genre expansion, and zero-centered EQ curves.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **DSP Chain Redesign**: The current EQ pipeline has several gain-stacking issues (`+3dB` hardcoded offset + `2x` exaggeration multiplier) that cause muddiness and potential clipping. This plan removes them and replaces with a clean, zero-centered approach.

> [!WARNING]
> **Motorola/Dolby Atmos Bug**: The spatial audio conflict on Moto devices when Dolby Atmos is on requires disabling our Virtualizer/Reverb/LoudnessEnhancer when they fail to initialize on that specific session. This is a graceful degradation — we cannot override Dolby's exclusive audio session lock.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Card State Persistence**: Currently, card expand/collapse state is derived from feature toggles (`isAutoEqEnabled`, etc.), causing cards to open by default and play closing animations on app launch. Fix: persist expand state in DataStore.

