## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Volume Compensation Strategy**: With the +3dB offset removed, users may perceive a volume drop when EQ activates. Should we use `LoudnessEnhancer` at a fixed ~150mB (+1.5dB) when EQ is active to compensate? Or trust the cleaner signal? Current recommendation: no boost — zero-centered curves should be perceptually neutral.

> [!NOTE]
> **Existing Song Cache**: Users with cached genre results will have old genre classifications (e.g., "Electronic" instead of "EDM"). These will still map correctly via `getPresetForGenre()` partial matching. New detections will use the expanded genre list.

